<br>
One night before I finally finished this fight, I ran down there to play around with the adds.  I was curious exactly how long the range was to leash them.  I found out if you run them TOWARDS the WW zoneline, they take longer to leash, or at least have a much longer boundary going that direction.  If you kite them even a little towards the ramp opposite the event, they leash very soon and kiting is nearly impossible.  If my thinking is correct, you can fairly easily have rangers and CC keeping the adds busy in that small space just before you get to the ramp and setup spot.  That is, have them kite and do whatever towards the zoneline.  If you don't go to far you won't leash them, but I would advise playing around with this beforehand to establish a &quot;leash line&quot; that the kiters cannot cross.  It's possible, or so I think <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=994568" target="top">Sedenten Van'Oranje</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
